																				<div class="sg-editor">
						
<p>Your triceps are crucial for improving overall arm strength and definition. They are prime movers in many <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-tricep-exercises" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">tricep exercises with dumbbells</a> and daily activities involving lifting, pulling, and carrying. They are prominent upper-arm muscles and contribute to achieving an aesthetically pleasing and sculpted upper body. </p>



<p>In this article, we discuss eight tricep workouts for beginners to enhance their tricep strength and target <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6950543/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">muscle hypertrophy</a>. They are straightforward and customizable for any fitness level making them beneficial for beginners. Most primarily target tricep isolation and development, but some are <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4592763/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">compound movements</a> that also work other muscle groups.</p>



<p>Read on for all the guidance you need to program these triceps exercises into your routine for optimal results.</p>



<div class="wp-block-group ft-snippet is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
<p class="has-medium-font-size">8 Must-Try Tricep Workouts For Beginners</p>



<p>Below you will discover 8 beneficial tricep workouts perfect for beginners to build strong arms. These exercises help new lifters prioritize their form while achieving their goals.</p>



<ul>
<li><a href="#Chair-Tricep-Dips">Chair Tricep Dips.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Push-Up">Push-Up.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Cable-Tricep-Pushdown">Cable Tricep Pushdown.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Cable-Tricep-Overhead-Extension">Cable Tricep Overhead Extension.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Tricep-Dips-Machine">Tricep Dips Machine.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Dumbbell-Tricep-Kickback">Dumbbell Tricep Kickback. </a></li>



<li><a href="#Dumbbell-Seated-Tricep-Extension">Dumbbell Seated Tricep Extension.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Dumbbell-Skull-Crusher">Dumbbell Skull Crusher.</a></li>
</ul>



<p>They can be customized and modified to fit various goals based on fitness level and experience.</p>
</div></div>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading list-start">Top 8 Tricep Workouts For Beginners</h2>



<p>The following workouts provide an accessible and effective stimulus for beginners to strengthen and build their triceps. Perform them as listed or in the order of your preference.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Chair-Tricep-Dips">Chair Tricep Dips</h3>



<p><a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/chair-tricep-dip" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Chair tricep dips</a> are a popular tricep strengthener that builds the triceps as well as the back, shoulders, and chest. This makes it a great part of <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/compound-tricep-exercises" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">compound tricep exercises</a> targeting multiple muscle groups at once.</p>



<p>Studies show the triceps can reach <a href="https://journals.lww.com/nsca-jscr/fulltext/2017/07000/maximal_strength_performance_and_muscle_activation.15.aspx" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">40%–50%</a> of maximum activation during weighted tricep extension. This provides an idea of how hard the muscle works during the pushing-up phase of this movement. </p>



<p>Chair tricep dips are great for beginners as they are extremely versatile and can be performed anywhere. They require only body weight and a sturdy chair or bench with a flat surface. They also benefit functional strength, targeting muscles involved in daily activities like lifting boxes and carrying groceries.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe title="Chair Tricep Dips" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/980219470?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Chair Tricep Dips Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How to do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Begin by standing in front of a sturdy chair or bench at about knee height.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>



<li>Sit on the bench with palms flat on the bench on either side of you (fingers pointing forward). Your legs should be extended out in front of you with your heels down for support.</li>



<li>Inhale as you engage your core and lower your upper body until your elbows are at a 90-degree angle.</li>



<li>Keep your back straight and core engaged throughout.</li>



<li>Exhale as you push back up, fully extending the arms back to the starting position.</li>



<li>Repeat for the desired reps and sets.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>This can be performed using any flat, sturdy surface, increasing the versatility of the exercise.</li>



<li>Ensure that your core and spinal muscles are engaged throughout the movement.</li>



<li>Use stable and controlled movements and avoid swinging or using momentum through the range of motion.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets &amp; Reps</h4>



<div class="wp-block-group medicine-table is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
<figure class="wp-block-table table-custom h-title table-border" style="font-size:16px;font-style:normal;font-weight:500"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><thead><tr><th class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><p class="pri-color-1">Training Style</p></th><th class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left"><p class="pri-color-1">Sets</p></th><th class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><p class="pri-color-1">Reps</p></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Strength Training</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">3–5</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">4–6</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Hypertrophy</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">3–4</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">8–12</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Endurance Training</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">3–4</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">15–20</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Power Training</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">3–5</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">3–5 (Explosive)</td></tr></tbody></table><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Optimal Sets &amp; Reps of Chair Tricep Dips</figcaption></figure>
</div></div>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Push-Up">Push-Up</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/push-up" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">push-up</a> is a classic foundational bodyweight exercise that works your entire body. It primarily targets your chest and upper arms but also engages the core and spinal muscles to maintain stability. </p>



<p>There are a variety of <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/training/benefits-of-push-ups" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">push-up benefits</a> including building strength, enhancing core stability, and improving posture. This makes it a simple but worthwhile exercise for beginners to maximize their results.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe title="Push-Up" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/957562432?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Push-up Guide. Video: <span>Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</span></figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Begin in a plank position with your arms fully extended. Your hands should be placed under your shoulders.</li>



<li>Your legs should be extended behind you, forming a straight line with your body from your head to your feet.</li>



<li>Inhale to engage your core.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Slowly lower your chest down to the ground, flexing your elbows to 90 degrees.</li>



<li>Hold this position for a count, focusing on squeezing your chest, shoulders, and upper arms to maximize engagement.</li>



<li>Exhale to push back up to the starting position.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Repeat for the desired number of reps and sets.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Avoid straining your neck at any point and keep your back flat. This ensures your shoulders and core remain engaged to avoid straining the neck or upper spine.</li>



<li>Keep your upper arms steady throughout. Only your forearms should move to flex the elbows during the lowering phase.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Ensure your stance is not too wide creating unnecessary strain on the shoulders and lower back.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



<div class="wp-block-group medicine-table is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
