<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Cable-Tricep-Pushdown">Cable Tricep Pushdown</h3>



<p><a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/cable-tricep-pushdown" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Cable tricep pushdown</a> is a beneficial tricep exercise that uses a cable machine and handles attached to a pulley. It targets all three parts of the triceps brachii: the lateral, medial, and long heads. </p>



<p>The exercise stimulates tricep <a href="https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC8884877/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">muscle hypertrophy</a> by <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/tricep-cable-workouts" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">using the cable to work the triceps</a>. You pull a handle attached to the weighted cable machine straight down while standing. In addition to activating the triceps, it requires core support to maintain stability and control.  </p>



<p>This is a beneficial and relatively simple exercise for beginners as it builds tricep strength using targeted intensity.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe title="Cable Tricep Pushdown" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/987039381?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Cable Tricep Pushdown Guide. Video: <span>Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</span></figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Secure a handle attachment to the high pulley of a cable machine. Select a weight that aligns with your goals and fitness level.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Stand with feet shoulder-width apart and grab the handle with both hands using an overhand grip (palm facing down).</li>



<li>Keep a slight bend in your knees and lean forward a bit, keeping a straight back.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Keep your elbows close to your body, maintaining control.</li>



<li>Exhale and slowly press the handle downward by extending your elbows.</li>



<li>Perform the movement in a controlled manner until your arms are extended and your triceps are contracted.</li>



<li>Hold the position briefly while squeezing your triceps.</li>



<li>Inhale and slowly return the handle to the starting position.</li>



<li>Repeat for the desired reps and sets.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Do not lock your elbows completely at the bottom of the pushdown to avoid joint stress.</li>



<li>Maintain a slight bend in your knees and engage your core to prevent lower back strain.</li>



<li>Keep your wrists in a neutral position throughout the motion to avoid wrist injuries.</li>
</ul>



