<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Tricep-Dips-Machine">Tricep Dips Machine</h3>



<p>The tricep dips machine is a popular tricep resistance exercise for many gymgoers. They isolate the triceps as the prime movers using a lever tricep machine. They also work the chest, shoulders, and core, providing stability and support throughout the exercise.</p>



<p>This movement improves functional strength as the targeted muscles are all involved in daily tasks like lifting, pulling, and carrying. It is versatile and relatively easy to perform, making it a great tricep workout for beginners.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="Tricep Dips Machine" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/997777218?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Tricep Dips Machine Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Begin by loading your appropriate weight to the tricep dip lever machine. Sit on the bench between the two parallel bars you will push down to lift the weight.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Grip the bars with palms facing inward to your torso and elbows flexed. Your feet should be flat on the ground.</li>



<li>Inhale as you engage your core.</li>



<li>Exhale as you push down on the bars, lifting the weights. Continue to fully extend your arms.</li>



<li>Hold at the bottom for a count, squeezing the triceps.</li>



<li>Inhale as you flex your elbows and let the bars lift back to the starting position.</li>



<li>Repeat for the desired reps and sets.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Don’t lock your elbows at the bottom of the movement as this can strain the joint. Keep a slight bend in the elbow.</li>



<li>Avoid letting the weights drop when you complete each rep. Maintain controlled and steady movements throughout.</li>



<li>Focus on squeezing your triceps to activate the <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26700744/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">mind-muscle connection</a> and maximize target muscle engagement.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



