<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Dumbbell-Seated-Tricep-Extension">Dumbbell Seated Tricep Extension</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-overhead-tricep-extension" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">dumbbell seated tricep extension</a> effectively isolates the triceps due to the resistance applied while in the overhead position. This uniquely stimulates the muscle for targeted strength gains. </p>



<p>The overhead stretching action promotes <a href="https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1080/17461391.2022.2100279" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">tricep muscle lengthening</a>. By fatiguing the muscles at their maximum length, you contribute to muscle fiber breakdown helping them rebuild stronger and larger. </p>



<p>This exercise is great for beginners as it also engages the core to maintain a stable, straight back. This supports posture, therefore enhancing lifting performance and general <a href="https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s11332-023-01129-w" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">quality of life</a>. </p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="Dumbbell Overhead Tricep Extension" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/982969469?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Dumbbell Seated Tricep Extension Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Select a dumbbell with a weight that aligns with your goals and fitness level. Sit on an upright bench holding the dumbbell with your feet flat on the floor.</li>



<li>Lift the dumbbell with both hands so you’re holding it behind your upper back and head. Your arms should be close to your ears, and your elbows bent upward as much as possible.</li>



<li>Inhale and engage your core.</li>



<li>Exhale and extend your arms straight toward the ceiling.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Hold briefly at the top position, focusing on squeezing the triceps.</li>



<li>Inhale and bend your elbows, lowering the dumbbell behind your head back to the starting position.</li>



<li>Repeat for the desired number of reps and sets.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Focus on bracing your core for the duration of the movement. If you feel your lower back starting to arch, decrease some of the weight.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Control the descent of the dumbbell to the starting position, avoiding swinging or using momentum.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Do not flare the elbows to the sides as this strains the shoulder joints. Keep your elbows tucked into the side of your face.</li>
</ul>



